{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"bd49da66-261b-4013-b02c-4424eb389305","content":"With MSTest 3.8.2 on .NET 9, here's the recommended approach:\n\n**Use constructor + `IAsyncInitialization` pattern:**\n\n```csharp\n[TestClass]\npublic class MyTests : IAsyncInitialization\n{\n    public TestContext TestContext { get; set; } = default!;\n\n    // Synchronous init via constructor\n    public MyTests()\n    {\n        // sync setup here\n    }\n\n    // Async init via TestInitialize\n    [TestInitialize]\n    public async Task SetupAsync()\n    {\n        // async per-test setup here\n        await SomeServiceAsync();\n    }\n\n    [TestMethod]\n    public void MyTest() { /* ... */ }\n}\n```\n\n**Key points:**\n\n- **`TestContext`** — declare a public property with `{ get; set; }`. MSTest injects it automatically (no constructor injection needed).\n- **Sync init** — use the constructor or a `[TestInitialize]` method.\n- **Async init** — use `[TestInitialize]` with an `async Task` signature.\n- **Class-level (one-time) async setup** — use `[ClassInitialize]` with signature `public static async Task ClassInit(TestContext context)`.\n\n```csharp\n[ClassInitialize]\npublic static async Task ClassInit(TestContext context)\n{\n    // one-time async setup for the class\n}\n\n[ClassCleanup]\npublic static async Task ClassCleanup()\n{\n    // one-time async teardown\n}\n```\n\nThis is the idiomatic pattern for MSTest v3+.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"146fe266-cda6-4893-9920-2ec8f0402b6b","outputTokens":384,"requestId":"BC54:D447C:1DEAA4F:212864F:69FA9725"},"id":"422f19b8-8507-4174-a5b5-4bfd58955d25","timestamp":"2026-05-06T01:19:43.016Z","parentId":"184153f9-9e56-4a58-9a6c-8b551118d6a1"}
